api.body:
require "pixcHelper"
require "pixcDriver"
--lock for not double init
if self.lock == true then return end
self.lock = true
if self.pixcHelper ~= nil then -- Init already called. call uninit before to reinit
	self.uninit()
	Utils.Timer.sleep(500)
end
self.lock = nil
--create helper and driver
self.pixcHelper = createPixcHelper(pixc,self())
self.driver = createPixcDriver()

--create self variable
self._powrIsOn = false
self._currentInpt = ""
self._connected = false
self.isAuth = false;
self.authHash = "";

-- set logfunction and connection state of projector
self.driver:setLogFunction(function (...) pixc.log(...) end)
self.driver:setConnectionLifecycleCallback(
	function(isConnected)
		self().IsConnected(isConnected, true)	
	end
)

--get all propertys
self.ip = self.pixcHelper:getProperty("IP","127.0.0.1")
self.State.IP(self.ip)
self.password = self.pixcHelper:getProperty("Password","")
self.autoReconnect = self.pixcHelper:getProperty("AutoReconnect","3s")
self.port = tonumber(self.pixcHelper:getProperty("Port","4352"))
--create tcp connection with auto reconnect all 3sec if disconnected
self.driver:set("tcp",self.ip,self.port,nil,nil,nil,self.autoReconnect or "3s");
self.driver:createParser()
--Matcher Error
self.driver:addMatcher("rError", '"%1ERST=" string(&0,{\r})',
    true,function (a,b) self().State.receive("ERST",a) end)
--Matcher Lamp Information
self.driver:addMatcher("rLamp", '"%1LAMP=" string(&0,{\r})',
    true,function (a,b) self().State.receive("LAMP",a) end)
--Matcher %1
self.driver:addMatcher("rPowr", '"%1" string(&0,{=},[5]) number(&1) "\r"',
    true,function (a,b) self().State.receive(a,b) end)
--Matcher %2
self.driver:addMatcher("rVers", '"%2" string(&0,{=},[5]) string(&1,{\r})',
    true,function (a,b) self().State.receive(a,b) end)
--Matcher Login
self.driver:addMatcher("rLoginNoAuto", '"PJLINK 0\r"',
    true,function () self().State.receiveNoAuth() end)
--Matcher Login Error
self.driver:addMatcher("rLoginError", '"PJLINK ERRA\r"',
    true,function () self().State.loginError() end)
--Matcher Authentification
self.driver:addMatcher("rLoginAuth", '"PJLINK 1 " string(&0,[8])"\r"',
    true,function(v) self().State.receiveAuth(v) end)
--Connect to Projector
self.driver:connectAsync();
--clear Interval for not add second
if self.interval ~= nil then
	pixc.getRoot().Utils.Timer.clearInterval(self.interval);
end
--add Interval call check State every 5sec
self.interval = pixc.getRoot().Utils.Timer.setInterval(
	function()
		self.State.checkState()
	end, 5000)
api.name: init

api.body:
--remove interval
if self.interval ~= nil then
	pixc.getRoot().Utils.Timer.clearInterval(self.interval);
	self.interval = nil
end
--remove helper
self.pixcHelper = nil
if self.driver == nil then return end
self.driver:close()
self.driver = nil
api.name: uninit

self._connected = pixcCommon.execAttribute(0, self._connected, isConnected, doSet)
if(self._connected == false) then
	self.authHash = ""
	
end
if(self._connected) then
	self.LoginOK("",true)
end
return self._connected

elems.body:
if self._loginOK ~= "OK" then
	self.LoginOK("OK",true)
end
if cmd == "POWR" then
	if val == 0 then
		self.State.PowerIsOn(false,true)
	elseif val == 1 then
		self.State.PowerIsOn(true,true)
	elseif val == 2 then
		self.State.PowerIsOn("Cooling",true)
	elseif val == 3 then
		self.State.PowerIsOn("WarmUp",true)
	end
elseif cmd == "SVER" then
	self.State.Version(val)
elseif cmd == "IRES" then
	self.State.InputResolution(val)
elseif cmd == "LAMP" then
	local t = self.pixcHelper.stringSplit(val," ")
	local offset = 1
	for i=1,#t/2,1 do
		self.State.Lamp["Lamp" .. i]["Hour"](t[offset])
		self.State.Lamp["Lamp" .. i]["On"](t[offset+1] == "1",true)
		self.State.Lamp["Lamp" .. i]["Style"]("unhide",true)
		offset = offset+2
	end
	for i=#t/2+1,8,1 do
		local c = math.floor(math.abs(i))
		self.State.Lamp["Lamp" .. c]["Hour"]("")
		self.State.Lamp["Lamp" .. c]["On"]("")
		self.State.Lamp["Lamp" .. c]["Style"]("hide",true)
	end
elseif cmd == "ERST" then
	local errorMsg = ""
	local t={}
	val:gsub(".",function(c) table.insert(t,c) end)
	if t[1] == "1" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Fan Warning \r"
	elseif t[1] == "2" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Fan Error \r"
	end
	if t[2] == "1" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Lamp Warning \r"
	elseif t[2] == "2" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Lamp Error \r"
	end
	if t[3] == "1" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Temp Warning \r"
	elseif t[3] == "2" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Temp Error \r"
	end
	if t[4] == "1" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Cover Open Warning \r"
	elseif t[4] == "2" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Cover Open Error \r"
	end
	if t[5] == "1" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Filter Warning \r"
	elseif t[5] == "2" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Filter Error \r"
	end
	if t[6] == "1" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Other Warning \r"
	elseif t[6] == "2" then
		errorMsg = errorMsg .. "Other Error \r"
	end
	self.State.ErrorState(errorMsg)
elseif cmd == "FREZ" then
	self.State.Freeze(val == "1", true)
elseif cmd == "AVMT" then
	self.State.Shutter(val == 31, true)
elseif cmd == "RRES" then
	self.State.RecommendedResolution(val)
elseif cmd == "INPT" then	
	if val == 0 then
		self.State.CurrentInput("None", true)
		return
	end
	if val == 11 then
		self.State.CurrentInput("RGB1", true)
		return
	end
	if val == 12 then
		self.State.CurrentInput("RGB2", true)
		return
	end
	if val == 31 then
		self.State.CurrentInput("DVI-D", true)
		return
	end
	if val == 32 then
		self.State.CurrentInput("HDMI", true)
		return
	end
	if val == 33 then
		self.State.CurrentInput("HDMI", true)
		return
	end
	if val == 34 then
		self.State.CurrentInput("SDI1", true)
		return
	end
	if val == 35 then
		self.State.CurrentInput("SDI2", true)
		return
	end
end
